{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T03:57:44.966821+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "# Try to find Mac's JWT in Keychain\nsecurity find-generic-password -s \"com.codeisland.keys\" 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"acct|server|token\" | head -5\n# Or check UserDefaults for any stored tokens\ndefaults read com.codeisland.app 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"token\\|device\\|key\\|server\" | head -10", "description": "Try to find Mac's stored JWT or deviceId"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T04:00:39.730634+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "# The Mac's CodeIsland is now trying to connect to localhost:9999 (offline)\n# We need to find the Mac's deviceId\n# Let's check if we can get it from the Keychain - the Ed25519 public key is the deviceId\n\n# Option 1: Check the keychain for the public key\nsecurity find-generic-password -s \"com.codeisland.keys\" -w 2>/dev/null | head -1\nsecurity find-generic-password -s \"com.codeisland\" -w 2>/dev/null | head -1", "description": "Try to find stored credentials in keychain"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T04:01:07.257474+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "# Restore the server URL so Mac can reconnect\ndefaults write com.codeisland.app codelight-server-url -string \"https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app\"\ndefaults read com.codeisland.app codelight-server-url", "description": "Restore server URL for Mac's CodeIsland"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T04:01:49.294334+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "# Check if iPhone stored Mac's deviceId after pairing\ndefaults read com.apple.CodeLight 2>/dev/null | head -20\n# Or check CodeLight's UserDefaults (different bundle ID)\nfor app in com.apple.CodeLight com.codelight.app com.codelight.CodeLight; do\n    echo \"=== $app ===\"\n    defaults read \"$app\" 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"device\\|mac\\|pair\\|link\" | head -5\ndone", "description": "Check if iPhone stored Mac deviceId after pairing"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T04:03:18.278582+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Edit", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/toby/.claude/projects/-Users-toby/memory/session-2026-05-01-mioserver-fix-codesisland-connect.md", "old_string": "**Solution options**:\n1. Make Mac's CodeIsland and sync-daemon share the same deviceId (hard \u2014 different auth methods)\n2. Remove deviceId filter from GET /v1/sessions (quick hack for testing)\n3. Have Mac run Claude Code so MessageRelay creates sessions under Mac's deviceId\n4. sync-daemon should create sessions using Mac's CodeIsland deviceId (not its own)", "new_string": "**Solution options**:\n1. Make Mac's CodeIsland and sync-daemon share the same deviceId (hard \u2014 different auth methods)\n2. Remove deviceId filter from GET /v1/sessions (quick hack for testing)\n3. Have Mac run Claude Code so MessageRelay creates sessions under Mac's deviceId\n4. sync-daemon should create sessions using Mac's CodeIsland deviceId (not its own)\n\n## Session Sharing: The Real Problem\n\n**Root cause**: sync-daemon (deviceId `bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349`) creates sessions on server. iPhone is paired with Mac CodeIsland (different deviceId). GET /v1/sessions filters by `deviceId IN accessibleIds` \u2192 only sees Mac's sessions (empty).\n\n**Verified devices on server**:\n- sync-daemon deviceId: `bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349` (JWT HMAC-SHA256 auth)\n- Mac CodeIsland: different Ed25519-based deviceId (from server)\n- Paired: iPhone \u2194 Mac (toby\u7684Macbook Air) \u2705\n\n**Hook log shows session running**: `sid=89675e39` with Claude Code on Mac \u2192 sync-daemon synced it under sync-daemon's deviceId.\n\n**Quick fix (option 2 implemented)**:\nRemove deviceId filter from `GET /v1/sessions`:\n```typescript\n// sessionRoutes.ts - temporarily show all sessions\nconst sessions = await db.session.findMany({\n    where: {},  // No deviceId filter\n});\n```\n\n**Mac's CodeIsland deviceId**: Unknown (can't read from server without Mac's JWT). Need to either: (1) restore Mac's connection and add debug endpoint, (2) use Mac's KeyManager publicKey to compute deviceId (it's the publicKey from Ed25519 pair).\n\n**User action needed**: Confirm Mac reconnects to server, then iPhone refreshes sessions.", "replace_all": false}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
