{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T11:59:56.935670+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "python3 -c \"\nimport sys, time, json, base64, hmac, hashlib\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\n\nfrom sync_daemon.http_client import HttpClient, _make_jwt\n\n# Simulate full startup with new config\nhttp = HttpClient(\n    base_url='https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app',\n    device_id='bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349',\n    jwt_secret='3a662d86367b9d6dcf0d8d6ca4b63748a37017a13a8fa5334817bdb952eef610',\n    outbox_path='/tmp/test-outbox.jsonl',\n)\n\nprint('Step 1: resolve Mac shortCode...')\nmac_id = http.fetch_mac_device_id('2JF3CM')\nprint(f'  Mac deviceId: {mac_id}')\nif not mac_id:\n    print('FAILED: could not resolve Mac deviceId')\n    sys.exit(1)\n\nhttp.session_device_id = mac_id\n\nprint('Step 2: check JWT claims for session creation...')\nheaders = http._auth_headers()\ntoken = headers['Authorization'].split(' ')[1]\n_, payload_b64, _ = token.split('.')\npadding = 4 - len(payload_b64) % 4\npayload = json.loads(base64.urlsafe_b64decode(payload_b64 + '=' * padding).decode())\nprint(f'  JWT deviceId claim: {payload[\\\"deviceId\\\"]} (should be Mac deviceId)')\nassert payload['deviceId'] == 'cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3', f'Wrong deviceId: {payload[\\\"deviceId\\\"]}'\n\nprint('Step 3: try to create a test session (idempotent)...')\ntest_tag = f'test-{int(time.time())}'\nresult = http.create_session(test_tag, '{\\\"path\\\":\\\"/tmp/test\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"test\\\",\\\"projectName\\\":\\\"test\\\"}')\nprint(f'  Session created/resolved: id={result.id}, deviceId={result.device_id}')\nassert result.device_id == 'cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3', f'Wrong session deviceId: {result.device_id}'\n\nprint('ALL CHECKS PASSED \u2014 sync-daemon sessions will now appear under Mac deviceId')\n\" 2>&1", "timeout": 30000, "description": "Verify full sync-daemon chain"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T12:01:43.611440+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "TOKEN=\"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJkZXZpY2VJZCI6ImJkZDA2YjQ5MGYyZDRjOTY4NDJjNDk4YzVkMzIxMzQ5IiwiaWF0IjoxNzc3NjM2MjcxLCJleHAiOjE3Nzc2Mzk4NzF9.cZZCgwPQMt9Nc_JvI8gndhodPDFhs_DgytRt7BdvdWc\"\ncurl -s \"https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app/v1/sessions\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(f'  {s[\\\"id\\\"][:20]} owner={s[\\\"ownerDeviceId\\\"][:20]} active={s[\\\"active\\\"]}') for s in data['sessions']]\"", "description": "Check current sessions after test"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T12:03:38.801078+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/toby/.claude/projects/-Users-toby/memory/mio-two-path-session-creation-2026-05-01.md", "content": "# MioServer Two-Path Session Creation \u2014 FIX APPLIED (2026-05-01)\n\n## Root Cause (confirmed)\n\niPhone CodeLight shows no sessions because:\n- sync-daemon creates sessions with `deviceId = bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349` (HS256 JWT, daemon's own deviceId)\n- Mac CodeIsland creates sessions with `deviceId = cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3` (Ed25519, Mac's Prisma UUID)\n- iPhone `MacSessionListView` filters: `filter { $0.ownerDeviceId == mac.deviceId }` \u2192 never matches sync-daemon sessions\n\n## Fix Implemented (2026-05-01): sync-daemon uses Mac's deviceId\n\n**Constraint**: User said \"\u53ea\u6539sync-daemon\uff0ccodeisland\u4e0d\u8981\u78b0\" \u2014 only modify sync-daemon, don't touch CodeIsland.\n\n**Solution**: sync-daemon resolves Mac's deviceId via server shortCode lookup, then uses Mac's deviceId in JWT claims when creating sessions.\n\n### Changes: MioServer\n\n**File**: `sources/devices/devicesRoutes.ts`\n```typescript\n// NEW endpoint: GET /v1/devices/mac-by-code/:shortCode\n// sync-daemon calls this on startup to resolve Mac's deviceId\napp.get('/v1/devices/mac-by-code/:shortCode', {\n    preHandler: authMiddleware,\n    schema: {\n        params: z.object({ shortCode: z.string().min(4).max(12) }),\n    },\n}, async (request, reply) => {\n    const { shortCode } = request.params as { shortCode: string };\n    const normalized = shortCode.toUpperCase().trim();\n    const mac = await db.device.findUnique({\n        where: { shortCode: normalized },\n        select: { id: true, name: true, kind: true },\n    });\n    if (!mac) return reply.code(404).send({ error: 'No Mac found with that shortCode' });\n    if (mac.kind !== 'mac') return reply.code(400).send({ error: 'That shortCode belongs to a non-Mac device' });\n    return { deviceId: mac.id, name: mac.name };\n});\n```\n- Mac shortCode confirmed: `\"2JF3CM\"` (name: \"toby\u7684MacBook Air\", deviceId: `cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3`)\n\n**File**: `sources/session/sessionRoutes.ts`\n```typescript\n// POST /v1/sessions: back-fill publicKey for devices created without one,\n// WITHOUT overwriting real Ed25519 publicKey values\nconst existing = await db.device.findFirst({ where: { id: deviceId } });\nif (!existing) {\n    await db.device.create({ data: { id: deviceId, name: 'Claude Code Sync', kind: 'mac', publicKey: deviceId } });\n} else if (!existing.publicKey || existing.publicKey === deviceId) {\n    await db.device.update({ where: { id: deviceId }, data: { publicKey: deviceId } });\n}\n```\n- Prevents Ed25519 device publicKey from being overwritten by sync-daemon's backfill\n\n### Changes: sync-daemon\n\n**File**: `config.yaml`\n```yaml\ndeviceId: \"bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349\"   # daemon's own deviceId (for auth)\nmacShortCode: \"2JF3CM\"                          # Mac's shortCode (resolves to Mac deviceId)\n```\n\n**File**: `sync_daemon/http_client.py`\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass HttpClient:\n    base_url: str\n    device_id: str\n    jwt_secret: str\n    session_device_id: str | None = None   # NEW: if set, use this in JWT claims instead of device_id\n\n    def _auth_headers(self) -> dict[str, str]:\n        iat = int(time.time())\n        effective_id = self.session_device_id or self.device_id\n        token = _make_jwt(effective_id, self.jwt_secret, iat)\n        return { \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {token}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" }\n\n    def fetch_mac_device_id(self, short_code: str) -> str | None:\n        # GET /v1/devices/mac-by-code/:shortCode \u2192 returns {deviceId, name}\n        path = f\"/v1/devices/mac-by-code/{urllib.parse.quote(short_code.upper().strip())}\"\n        resp = self._request(\"GET\", path)\n        if resp.ok:\n            return resp.json().get(\"deviceId\")\n        return None\n```\n\n**File**: `sync_daemon/__main__.py`\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass Config:\n    device_id: str\n    jwt_secret: str\n    server_url: str\n    jsonl_path: str\n    mac_short_code: str = \"\"  # NEW\n\ndef load_config(path):\n    # reads macShortCode from config.yaml or SYNC_MAC_SHORT_CODE env var\n    mac_short_code = get(\"macShortCode\", \"SYNC_MAC_SHORT_CODE\")\n    ...\n\ndef main():\n    http = HttpClient(...)\n    # On startup: resolve Mac deviceId if shortCode configured\n    session_device_id: str | None = None\n    if config.mac_short_code:\n        session_device_id = http.fetch_mac_device_id(config.mac_short_code)\n        if session_device_id:\n            http.session_device_id = session_device_id\n            logger.info(\"Mac deviceId resolved: %s\", session_device_id[:8])\n        else:\n            logger.warning(\"Could not resolve Mac deviceId for shortCode '%s'\", config.mac_short_code)\n```\n\n### Verification\n\n```python\n# All checks passed:\nStep 1: resolve Mac shortCode \u2192 cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3 \u2705\nStep 2: JWT deviceId claim = Mac deviceId \u2705\nStep 3: new session belongs to Mac deviceId \u2705\n\n# Railway logs confirmed:\nGET /v1/devices/mac-by-code/2JF3CM  # returning {deviceId, name}\nPOST /v1/sessions                   # session deviceId = cmol0jn... (Mac's)\n```\n\n### Deploy\n\n- MioServer commit `3d2b060` pushed to `123qwe55aa/MioServer.git`\n- Railway build `3af22973` deployed and SUCCESS\n- mac-by-code endpoint confirmed working on Railway\n\n## Device Ids\n| Source | Auth | deviceId | For Sessions |\n|--------|------|----------|-------------|\n| sync-daemon (auth) | HS256 JWT | `bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349` | (unchanged, for auth only) |\n| sync-daemon (sessions) | HS256 JWT | `cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3` | Mac's deviceId \u2705 |\n| Mac CodeIsland | Ed25519 | `cmol0jn730000p98xplelsws3` | Mac's deviceId \u2705 |\n\n## Next Steps\n- Restart sync-daemon on remote machine to pick up new config\n- New sessions will appear under Mac deviceId \u2192 visible on iPhone\n- Old sessions (deviceId=bdd06b...) won't show on iPhone \u2014 use debug endpoint to clean up"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
