nt + server endpoint \u5df2\u5bf9\u9f50 |\n| iPhone CodeLight \u8f6e\u8be2\u80fd\u770b\u5230\u8fdc\u7a0b CC session | \u5b8c\u6210 | \u901a\u8fc7 Mac deviceId owner \u5bf9\u9f50\u4fee\u590d |\n| \u6d88\u606f\u4e0d\u91cd\u590d | \u57fa\u672c\u5b8c\u6210 | server localId \u53bb\u91cd\uff1b\u4f46\u591a text block id \u9700\u4fee |\n| \u5d29\u6e83\u540e\u91cd\u542f\u7eed\u4f20 | \u57fa\u672c\u5b8c\u6210 | session cache + watcher state + outbox \u5df2\u5b9e\u73b0\uff1bincomplete line offset bug \u9700\u4fee |\n| \u5355\u5143\u6d4b\u8bd5\u8986\u76d6 core \u6a21\u5757 | \u90e8\u5206\u5b8c\u6210 | \u8986\u76d6\u5b58\u5728\uff0c\u4f46\u5f53\u524d\u6709 1 \u4e2a\u8fc7\u671f\u65ad\u8a00\u5931\u8d25 |\n\n## 6. \u5f52\u6863\u51b3\u5b9a\n\nTASK-007 \u53ef\u4ee5\u5f52\u6863\uff0c\u7406\u7531\uff1a\n\n1. \u4e3b\u94fe\u8def\u5df2\u7ecf\u4ece JSONL \u5230 server \u5230 iPhone \u6253\u901a\u3002\n2. \u6700\u5173\u952e\u7684 device ownership mismatch \u5df2\u4fee\u590d\u5e76\u9a8c\u8bc1\u3002\n3. \u5269\u4f59\u95ee\u9898\u662f\u53ef\u9760\u6027/\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4fee\u6b63\u7c7b\u540e\u7eed\u9879\uff0c\u4e0d\u963b\u585e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u529f\u80fd\u4f7f\u7528\u3002\n\n\u5efa\u8bae\u65b0\u5f00\u540e\u7eed\u4efb\u52a1\uff1a\n\n- TASK-008\uff1a\u4fee\u590d sync-daemon parser offset \u4e0e block id \u5b8c\u6574\u6027\u3002\n- TASK-009\uff1a\u6062\u590d MioServer session list \u6743\u9650\u8fc7\u6ee4\uff0c\u79fb\u9664 personal TEMP HACK\u3002\n- TASK-010\uff1a\u8865 CodeLight app \u6e90\u7801\u5ba1\u67e5\u4e0e UI \u94fe\u8def\u56de\u5f52\u6d4b\u8bd5\u3002\n"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T12:32:01.810701+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon", "tool": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/toby/Documents/RTS/agent-shared/tasks/TASK-007/review.md", "content": "# TASK-007 Code Review\n\n**Reviewed**: 2026-05-01\n**Decision**: APPROVE FOR ARCHIVE WITH FOLLOW-UP FIXES\n\n## Summary\n\nTASK-007 \u7684\u4e3b\u6d88\u606f\u94fe\u8def\u5df2\u7ecf\u6253\u901a\uff1aClaude Code JSONL \u2192 sync-daemon \u2192 MioServer \u2192 CodeLight/CodeIsland \u53ef\u89c1 session/message\u3002\u6700\u5173\u952e\u7684 ownerDeviceId \u4e0d\u4e00\u81f4\u95ee\u9898\u5df2\u901a\u8fc7 `macShortCode` \u2192 Mac deviceId lookup \u4fee\u590d\u3002\n\n\u672c\u6b21\u5ba1\u67e5\u4ecd\u53d1\u73b0 2 \u4e2a HIGH \u7ea7\u53ef\u9760\u6027\u95ee\u9898\u548c 1 \u4e2a server \u6743\u9650\u6a21\u578b\u540e\u7eed\u9879\u3002\u5b83\u4eec\u4e0d\u963b\u585e TASK-007 \u5f52\u6863\uff0c\u4f46\u5e94\u62c6\u6210\u540e\u7eed\u4efb\u52a1\u4fee\u590d\u3002\n\n## Files Reviewed\n\n### sync-daemon\n\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/sync_daemon/__main__.py`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/sync_daemon/http_client.py`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/sync_daemon/jsonl_watcher.py`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/sync_daemon/message_parser.py`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/sync_daemon/session_mgr.py`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/sync-daemon/tests/*.py`\n\n### MioServer / CodeServer\n\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/MioServer/sources/auth/middleware.ts`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/MioServer/sources/auth/crypto.ts`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/MioServer/sources/auth/deviceAccess.ts`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/MioServer/sources/devices/devicesRoutes.ts`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/MioServer/sources/session/sessionRoutes.ts`\n\n### CodeIsland\n\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/ClaudeIsland/Services/Sync/MessageRelay.swift`\n- `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland/ClaudeIsland/Services/Sync/ServerConnection.swift`\n- Prior known reference: `ClaudeIsland/Services/Session/ConversationParser.swift`\n\n### CodeLight\n\n- Local repo `/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeLight` only contains `packages/CodeLightCrypto` and `packages/CodeLightProtocol`; app source such as `MacSessionListView` is not present locally. CodeLight app review is therefore based on known server fields and observed behavior, not per-file static review.\n\n## Findings\n\n### CRITICAL\n\nNone.\n\n### HIGH\n\n#### HIGH 1 \u2014 Incomplete JSONL line can be skipped by offset advancement\n\n- `sync_daemon/message_parser.py:239-248`\n- `sync_daemon/jsonl_watcher.py:284-295`\n\n`parse_messages_since()` intentionally defers incomplete trailing lines, but `_process_file()` persists EOF as `last_offset` afterward. A partial JSONL line can be skipped once it is completed.\n\nSuggested fix: parser should return the last consumed offset; watcher should persist only the offset after the last complete line.\n\n#### HIGH 2 \u2014 Multi-text block messages can be dropped by UUID dedupe\n\n- `sync_daemon/message_parser.py:377-387`\n- `sync_daemon/message_parser.py:423-433`\n- `sync_daemon/message_parser.py:265-269`\n\nBlock-expanded messages may reuse `msg_uuid`. Dedupe by UUID can drop valid later text blocks from the same JSONL message.\n\nSuggested fix: use stable per-block IDs: `{msg_uuid}-text-{index}`, `{msg_uuid}-thinking-{index}`, while preserving tool IDs for tool_use/tool_result.\n\n### MEDIUM\n\n#### MEDIUM 1 \u2014 Watcher state accepts persisted file paths without root validation\n\n- `sync_daemon/jsonl_watcher.py:128-146`\n\nA tampered state file can restore arbitrary paths. Normalize and require restored paths to be under watcher root.\n\n#### MEDIUM 2 \u2014 Parser reads full tail chunk into memory\n\n- `sync_daemon/message_parser.py:229-232`\n\nLarge append bursts can cause unnecessary memory pressure. Prefer streaming line-by-line or bounded chunks.\n\n#### MEDIUM 3 \u2014 MioServer session list still contains temporary global visibility hack\n\n- `MioServer/sources/session/sessionRoutes.ts:106-122`\n\n`accessibleIds` is computed but not used; the query returns all active/recent sessions. This is acceptable for Toby's personal debugging but should not remain in a production permission model.\n\nSuggested fix: use `deviceId: { in: accessibleIds }` with active/recent filtering once no longer debugging.\n\n### LOW\n\n#### LOW 1 \u2014 Test result document is stale\n\n- `agent-shared/tasks/TASK-007/test-results.md:12`\n\nDocument says `98 passed`; current run is `97 passed, 1 failed`. The failing assertion expects old JWT `sub` claim, while implementation and MioServer use `deviceId` claim.\n\n## Validation Results\n\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| sync-daemon pytest | FAIL: 97 passed, 1 failed |\n| Failure | `tests/test_http_client.py::TestMakeJwt::test_payload_contains_subject` expects `sub`; current JWT payload uses `deviceId` |\n| MioServer static review | Completed manually |\n| CodeIsland static review | Completed manually for sync files |\n| CodeLight app static review | Skipped: app source unavailable locally |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Status\n\n| Criteria | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Read CC JSONL files | Met with caveat: incomplete trailing line bug |\n| POST messages to MioServer | Met |\n| iPhone CodeLight can see sessions | Met after Mac deviceId owner alignment |\n| localId dedupe | Mostly met; block-expanded IDs need hardening |\n| Restart resume | Mostly met; offset advancement bug needs fix |\n| Unit tests | Partially met; one stale JWT assertion failing |\n\n## Final Decision\n\n`APPROVE FOR ARCHIVE WITH FOLLOW-UP FIXES`\n\nTASK-007 should be archived because the intended product path is working and the device ownership mismatch is resolved. The HIGH findings should become follow-up reliability tasks rather than keeping TASK-007 open indefinitely.\n"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
